{"questionId":"22575164","questionHtml":"<p>By differentiating both sides of the above equation with respect to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>r</mi></math>, find an expression for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><munderover><mo>∑</mo><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mo>∞</mo></munderover><mi>n</mi><mi>a</mi><msup><mi>r</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math> in terms of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>r</mi></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>LHS:</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>a</mi><mi>r</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>a</mi><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mo>…</mo></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>A1</strong></em> for writing LHS <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Σ</mi><mi>a</mi><msup><mi>r</mi><mi>n</mi></msup></math> and differentiating to get <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Σ</mi><mi>a</mi><mi>n</mi><msup><mi>r</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>RHS:</p>\n<p>attempt to differentiate <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>r</mi></mrow></mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math> or use quotient rule&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>a</mi><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>r</mi></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><munderover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Σ</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mo>∞</mo></munderover><mi>n</mi><mi>a</mi><msup><mi>r</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>a</mi><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>r</mi></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> To award the final <em><strong>A1</strong></em> “<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><munderover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Σ</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mo>∞</mo></munderover><mi>n</mi><mi>a</mi><msup><mi>r</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>” must be seen either as part of the LHS working or as part of the final answer and all previous marks must be awarded.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><strong><em>[4 marks]</em></strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22575164","referenceCode":"24M.3.AHL.TZ1.1ci","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"By differentiating both sides of the above equation with respect to r, find an expression for ∑n=1∞narn-1 in terms of a and r.","paper":"3","level":"HL","questionNumber":"i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 4]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5 —Calculus","Topic 5 —Calculus","SL 5.6—Differentiating polynomials n E Q. Chain, product and quotient rules"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}